<div><div><h2>Nickel futures up on global cues, spot demand</h2></div><div>"nickel prices rose by 0.30 per cent in futures trade on tuesday as speculators raised their bets amid a firming trend overseas and spot demand.at the multi commodity exchange nickel for delivery in november gained rs 21.40 or 0.30 per cent to rs 798.70 per kg in a business turnover of 367 lots.analysts said apart from increased domestic demand from alloy-makers firmness in the base metals in overseas influenced nickel prices at futures trade."</div></div>